    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently `:connect ssh://` requires OpenSSH ControlMaster for multiplexing, which is not supported by Win32-OpenSSH (https://github.com/PowerShell/Win32-OpenSSH/issues/1328)\n\nVSCode Remote SSH has the same limitation (https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-remote-release/issues/96) - they work around it by opening separate SSH connections instead of multiplexing.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWe could take a similar approach to support Windows clients in the future.\n\nRelated PR: #39378",
